HEADWORD: Cocculus Indicus
<hw>Coc"cu*lus In"di*cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>cocculus</ets> (dim. of L. <ets>coccum</ets> kermes berry) + L.
<ets>Indicus</ets> of India.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The fruit or
berry of the <spn>Anamirta Cocculus</spn>, a climbing plant of the East
Indies. It is a poisonous narcotic and stimulant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

